# Project Structure

## Module Organization

- Modules represent features/capabilities (e.g., `orders`, `auth`, `cart`)
- Services are dependency-injectable solutions (e.g., `orders.service.ts`)
- Never create generic module names like `helpers.module.ts`
- Use feature-based organization, not type-based (not `controllers/`, `services/`)

## File Placement

- New feature → new module directory
- Shared utilities → `common/` or `shared/`
- External integrations → dedicated module (e.g., `braintree/`, `stripe/`)
- Config/constants → `config/` at module level

## Naming Conventions

| Type | Convention | Example |
|------|-----------|---------|
| Backend files | kebab-case | `order-processor.service.ts` |
| Frontend components | PascalCase | `OrderSummary.vue` |
| Frontend files | camelCase | `useOrderStore.ts` |
| Test files | same as source + `.spec` or `.test` | `order.service.spec.ts` |

## Do Not

- Add to index files (`index.ts`) — create specific utility files instead
- Create `utils.ts` mega-files — break into `string-utils.ts`, `date-utils.ts`, etc.
- Mix concerns in one file (DB access + business logic + HTTP handling)
